Russian Army Losses In Ukraine Exceed 1 Million Military Personnel
6
- 12.06.2025, 8:30
- 2,910
The Ukrainian General Staff has updated the data.
The army of aggressor country Russia has lost an estimated 1 million 340 military personnel in the war against Ukraine since the start of the full-scale invasion, the AFU General Staff reported on Thursday, June 12.
The aggressor's losses for the day are approximately 1,140. The General Staff also updated Russian losses in equipment:
tanks - 10,933 (plus six units over the day);
armored combat vehicles - 22,786 (+3);
artillery systems - 2,963 (+47);
RLS - 1,413;
air defense equipment - 1,184 (+1);
aircraft - 416;
helicopters - 337;
UAVs of operational-tactical level - 40435 (+138);
winged missiles - 3337;
ships/boats - 28;
submarines - 1;
vehicles and tankers - 51715 (+136);
special equipment - 3914.
